data.text:
Quezon City, Philippines

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 14.676208, 121.043861.

Quezon City is a very large and modern city which is located on Luzon island. Quezon City is a former capital and one of the richest cities in the Philippines. Together with the current capital city of Manila, as well as some other large cities like Makai, Pasai, and others, Quezon City is a part of a large urban area that is considered one of the largest in the Far East. The total area of Quezon City is estimated to be close to 64 miles and it is located to the north of Manila. Quezon City is an inland area bordered by Valenzuela, Caloocan, Marikina, Pasig, Mandaluyong, and other cities. This really busy and modern urban area can be found in the central part of Luzon Island, about 700 miles southwest of Hong Kong and about 720 miles south of the city of Taipei. It is a principal cultural and political center of the country, which contributes greatly to the country's economy and education. It is famous for its landmarks and attractions like Quezon Memorial Circle, the City's Arboretum Forest, UP-Ayala Land TechnoHub Central Park, and others. The northeastern part of the city is known as the place where a large nature preserve, La Mesa Watershed, is located. The park is famous for its small beautiful man-made lake, La Mesa Dam Reservoir, located there.
